@Node "Overview" "PrintManager.guide/Overview"

@{b}PrintManager? What is it?
*************************@{ub}

 PrintManager is a so called printer-spooler, it intercepts all printer.device
calls to the parallel-/serial.device and saves the printer specific raw data
to a file. This way, programs sending data to the printer don't have to wait 
for the slow printer to continue. PrintManager also gives you some control
over the data send to the printer. You can even print files directly from in-
side PrintManager using the datatypes-system.

 You probably know PrintManager 2.0 by Nicola Salmoria, both programs (mines
and Nicolas) look quite similar (which isn't really an accident:-), but no part
of my program bases on the program code of Nicolas' version.

@EndNode

@Node "ShareWare" "PrintManager.guide/Shareware"

@{b}PrintManager is Shareware
*************************@{ub}

 Please keep in mind that is program is SHAREWARE, if you like it please 
register your copy of PrintManager. Registered users will get a keyfile which 
removes the annoying shareware requesters and enables spooldrawer scanning 
at program start, so that older jobs can be recovered after a reset/crash. 
The menu-items Jobs/Save as ... and Settings/Fast Par? will also be enabled.

Price (only cash please):

 US$ 10.-
 DEM 15.-

@{i}If you want to get the keyfile by snail-mail, please add US$3.-/DEM 5.- to 
the registration fee.@{ui}

@{b}@{u}IMPORTANT:@{ub}@{uu} Don't forget to mention your full name and address when 
you register PrintManager.

@EndNode

